<h1 class="govuk-heading-l datagovuk-heading-l">Climate projections</h1>

<p class="govuk-body-m datagovuk-body">The UK Climate Projections (UKCP18) provides climate model projections for the UK, showing how the climate is likely to change in the future until 2100. You can access high-resolution, spatially-coherent future climate projections for the globe at 60km scale and for the UK at 12 km scale. The 12km climate model allows for realistic simulations of high-impact events such as localised heavy rainfall in summer, projections of sea-level rise and storm surges. </p>
<p class="govuk-body-m datagovuk-body">The data includes: </p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet datagovuk-list">
  <li>spreadsheets of results based on probabilistic and sea level projections</li>
<li>maps with projections over land for different variables across UK nations, administrative regions and river basins until 2099</li>

</ul>



